texts.text: For as long as I can remember, this voice has called to me...
"Someday, the envoy of the sun will come for thee."
"Your purpose in life involves just that."
No matter who I asked, I couldn't tell who's voice this was.
Most just wrote it off as a child's imagination running wild.
I learned that only I can hear this voice when I was in elementary school.
Shortly after that, I entered middle school.
Then my parents died. An accident had happened.
We were poor so there was nothing for them to leave me, and I had no other relatives.
I managed to receive welfare from the state to survive,
and I was forced to somehow make it on my own at a young age.
But I wasn't scared at all.
That voice... The one that kept calling upon me since I was little
told me the reason why I was born into this world.
I live to fulfill a certain purpose at a certain time.
And I could overcome anything as long as I kept that in mind.
Then that time came...

*Snicker*
Everything is ready.
All that is left to do is wait for my servant to arrive.
How vexing...
But the wheels are already turning. There is no need to fret...
>One day in Akihabara...
It's sooo hot...
It really is... Apparently, it's supposed to be 36°C today too.
Three days over 30°C... This is beyond unusual...
Right?! It's winter now. WINTER!
And didn't we get weird weather a few times the last few years too?
Like being freezing cold during summer or snowing in April?
But a heat wave in winter is just insane! This is messed up!
Don't look at me... It's not like I can do anything about it...
Maybe it's the sun? Something could be going on with it.
Like what...?
I don't know... It's just something that someone said online.
If only they'd let us switch back to our summer uniforms...
Three more people collapsed at my school today too.
Okay. Well, I'm this way so...
Oh, okay. Bye, Rika.
Try not to get sunburned...!
Phew... It was so hot... Huh?
S-Sorry for intruding!
S-Sorry...!
>A boy and a girl with little children in tow bow apologetically.
Guests? This is a rare sight.
They said they're here to see Megakin.
I just got here and heard from Meat Balloon.
I know that Megakin is popular with children,
but I didn't expect this. They seem very outgoing for their age.
Yo, I can hear y'all! There's nothin' fishy goin' on here.
There's this guy my age called Yoji,
and he's a priest.
Yo, he had me come over one time to play with them.
So we already know each other!
Wait, a priest invited you to his church? That needs more explaining...
I think he wanted Megakin to come and see us.
We're all orphans, but the church takes care of us.
Even then, the little ones feel really down sometimes.
Which is why I think he was invited, so that we'd have fun and laugh a little.
Just a bit of fan appreciation, am I right?
We put a little somethin' together so that kids from all over can come and play.
And you're Haruto, right? What brings you here today?
Somethin' you wanted to talk about?
Yes, um... Do you know where our priest went?
Nah... He didn't tell me anything' about goin' somewhere.
Oh, okay...
We were hoping that you'd know something about where he went...
Hmm... Yo, he doesn't seem like the type to just up and leave...
Exactly. So we're worried that something might've happened to him...
It's been three days...
The little ones are really starting to get scared too...
Hina...
>A little one starts tugging at the girl's skirt.
Don't worry. Come here...
We talked to the police top,
but they said that three days wasn't enough to start investigating anything.
Damn. That ain't good...
Yo, thanks for lettin' us know. We'll try helpin' too.
If we find anythin', we'll let you know right away.
Thank you...!
Oh, and um... There's this other thing...
They were so polite.
The oldest must've been a middle schooler at most too.
Yeah. They're still at an age where they should be cared for by an adult, at least in this country.
He's putting on a strong face, but is probably just as worried as the rest of them.
Yoji...
He lost his parents when he was that age too.
He talked to me about it when we were in school together, and since he became a priest,
he's made it his duty to look after kids goin' through the same thing.
Yo, he's really somethin' else. And when I told him that he responded,
"I lost my parents and had nowhere to go."
"Kids like that need somewhere to go and someone to support them."
"Until they do find a new home, I'll be there for them."
Yo, there's no way he'd just leave all those kids alone like this.
Yes, we need to find out what's going on for their sake.
Aight...
Oh, my bad. Seiran, you got somethin' for us?
This may seem like a non sequitur,
but a very strange Aura Gate has just appeared.
And that may be the cause of what's going on right now.
I'd like you to investigate but...
Should we hold off on it until you've found your friend, Megakin?
Myself, Gakuto and Seiran.
We might be able to get maybe one more before we head out.
Nah, it's all good. Thanks, y'all.
Yo, I gotta go check this thing out too. Lead the way, Seiran.
Okay... Looks like we all made it in.
The entrance took a while to find, but I felt something three days ago.
Right about when we started getting this strange weather.
I see. It does seem like they're connected then.
It's hot here too...
Yeah... This is bad... I'll shed weight just by being here.
(Three days... Yoji vanishing... They can't be connected...)
But this doesn't feel all that different from a normal Aura Gate.
I guess we should start looking around. Sound good, Megakin?
Hey...!
Y-Yeah. My bad... Let's take a quick look...
